==English==
BAROQUE
===etymology===
'''<Portuguese> rough pearl'''
#a pearl scuffed on one side from improper shipping and handling
===adjective===
'''baroque'''
#[[complex]] and [[beautiful]], yet for an outward irregularity
#having an [[irregular]] shape.
#[[intricate]], complex in texture
#[[ornate]], decorated, laden with detail

===noun===
'''a kind of architecture in the late middle ages'''
#where complex details are visible on every inch of a wall or facade
'''a kind of art in the late middle ages'''
#that attends to detail, often to excess
'''a chesslike game of exceptional complexity and beauty'''